Newcastle disease in Slovakia
----------------
(Date of previous outbreak of Newcastle disease in Slovakia reported
to the OIE: 1980).

Immediate notification report

Information received on 2 Nov 2005 from Prof. Jozef Bires, Director
General, State Veterinary and Food Administration (SVFA), Bratislava:

Report date: 2 Nov 2005.

Reason for immediate notification: re-occurrence of a listed disease
in a country.

Precise identification of agent: avian paramyxovirus 1 (APMV1), pigeon variant.

Date of first confirmation of the event: 26 Oct 2005.

Date of start of the event: 5 Oct 2005.

Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.

Details of outbreak:

First administrative division: Zilina
Lower administrative division: Zilina
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: Lietavska Lucka
Species: avi

Number of animals in the outbreak
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
150* / 14 / 0 / 150 / 0

* pigeons

Diagnosis
------
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed: State Veterinary
Laboratory, Zvolen (national reference laboratory)
Diagnostic tests used: - virus isolation in chicken embryos; -
haemagglutination inhibition test.
Date: 26 Oct 2005
Results: positive

Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed: State Veterinary
Laboratory, Zvolen (national reference laboratory)
Diagnostic tests used: sequencing
Date: 26 Oct 2005
Results: amino acid sequence on cleavage site: 111-Gly-Arg-
Arg-Lys-Lys-Arg-Phe-119

Source of outbreak or origin of infection: probably contact with town pigeons.

Control measures: in accordance with European Union legislation:
- within the zones, poultry cannot be moved without permission from SVFA;
- stamping out;
- cleaning and disinfection.

Vaccination prohibited: no.

Final report: no.

